item.title: How to change that
item.dc:creator: @Lord_of_fallen_Angel Lord of fallen Angels
item.description:
@Lord_of_fallen_Angel wrote:

If this is a custom interface, it is stored in the client. Possibly using a different client would help, unless the interface has just an overwirted text placed over it in a Class file. You would have to find the class file that’s declaring the method which is handling the interface procedure, and change the settings.

Read full topic

item.title: How to change that
item.dc:creator: @deathschaos9 DeathsChaos9
item.description:
@deathschaos9 wrote:

Its in the client. Not the server. Its a custom image. Go into your client folder and look in \Files\Files\interface

The name of that image is mainframe 0.png
